<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-10-05T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-10-05T02:00:00-05:00" n="249" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d249">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.77/1229.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-05T15:00:00+08:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">October 5, 1912—3 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>On September 30 the Belgian company that constructed railway Kaifeng
                                to Honan signed a new contract to build line from Haichou via
                                Kaifeng to Lanchou, in Kansuh, for 215,000,000 francs, the railway
                                to be security. When contract ratified, 5,000,000 taels will be paid
                                China, nominally to purchase line already constructed.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Calhoun.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>